title: Get the MMM data request history

headers.name: Access-Token
headers.description: Authorized access token. For details, see Authentication .

parameters.name: from_date
parameters.description: Start date, in the format of YYYY-MM-DD (UTC+0 time). The start date cannot be earlier than four years ago.

parameters.name: end_date
parameters.description: End date, in the format of YYYY-MM-DD (UTC+0 time).

top_fields.name: code
top_fields.description: Response code. For the complete list of response codes and descriptions, see Appendix-Return Code .

top_fields.name: message
top_fields.description: Response message. For details, see Appendix - Return Codes .

top_fields.name: request_id
top_fields.description: The log ID of a request, which uniquely identifies the request.

fields.name: historical_requests
fields.description: A JSON-formatted string array that displays historical requests, providing details for each request. For the fields media_type and Status , you might need to convert the returned integer values to string values in other MMM endpoints based on the following mapping: Supported values for media_type : 0 : corresponds to All . 1 : corresponds to Earned . 2 : corresponds to Paid . Supported values for Status : 1 : corresponds to request received . 3 : corresponds to in progress . 5 : corresponds to completed - ready for download . 2 : corresponds to failed . 4 : corresponds to failed .
